- Financial performance metrics include total revenue and net income;
- Stock market performance metrics include the average last traded price and total trading volume;
- The ranking is based on a composite of these metrics, giving higher weight to companies with higher total revenue, average stock price, and total trading volume.

- 'Consolidated financial statements' are financial statements that present the financial position, results of operations, and cash flows of a parent company and its subsidiaries as one economic entity;
- 'Year ending 2022' refers to the financial statements for the fiscal year ending on December 31, 2022;
- 'Total investment' is the sum of the quantity of stocks multiplied by the purchase price in the portfolio;
